 information in the inference of a triplet Q,b(x),K(x,h) from WS observations; (ii) the clear signatures of river bottom slope break in low flows and width variations in high flows, through the analysis of the friction slope term, which is consistent with the findings of Montazem et al. (2019) from WS curvature analysis.},
  file = {C\:\\Users\\craig\\Zotero\\storage\\BCQDAAMS\\Garambois et al. - 2020 - Variational estimation of effective channel and un.pdf;C\:\\Users\\craig\\Zotero\\storage\\II8R63VE\\S0022169419311448.html},
  journal = {Journal of Hydrology},
  keywords = {1D hydraulic model,Anabranching river,Hydraulic visibility,Satellite altimetry,SWOT,Ungauged river,Variational assimilation},
  language = {en}
}

